[SN]TITLE[SN]
Oxford United 2-4 Bolton Wanderers

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Bolton strengthened their grip on the second League One automatic promotion place after seeing off Oxford United.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Filipe Morais fired the Trotters ahead early after Simon Eastwood saved Gary Madine's header before Mark Beevers doubled the lead from close range.
Kane Hemmings gave Oxford hope before half-time but a Chey Dunkley own goal made it 3-1 to Bolton on the hour.
Chris Maguire's free-kick pulled another back for Oxford but Josh Vela's stoppage-time goal secured the points.
Bolton move four points clear of third-placed Fleetwood with eight games remaining, while Oxford's play-off hopes were dented by defeat as they remain ninth, five points off the top six.
